cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about image editing using neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes two novel neural network architectures for fast style transfer, which involves training deep neural networks to render an input content image using the visual style of arbitrary reference images. This task requires a combination of computer vision, artificial intelligence, and machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI and cs.LG also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the photorealistic stylization, which involves preserving rich details of the input content, and this could be related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
